Abstract\par
The Unified Quantum Gravity Model (UQGM) introduces the Information Density Field (IDF) as the fundamental structure of spacetime, unifying quantum mechanics, gravity, and cosmology under a single framework. By treating energy and information as equivalent, this model resolves longstanding mysteries such as dark matter, dark energy, and quantum gravity. The IDF framework provides testable predictions and offers new pathways for understanding the universe.\par
\par
1. Introduction\par
For decades, physicists have sought to unify the quantum world with the gravitational framework of general relativity. Attempts such as string theory and loop quantum gravity have provided insights but have not yielded a comprehensive, testable theory. The UQGM proposes a paradigm shift: spacetime is not a fundamental entity but an emergent phenomenon arising from the dynamic interplay of energy and information within the Information Density Field.\par
This paper lays the foundation for the UQGM by presenting the core principles, key equations, and initial validations, serving as the central hub for the accompanying modular papers that explore its implications across various domains of physics and mathematics.\par
